         <h3> Explain Me Please I'm the Average Joe</h3>
         <h5> History of Banks</h5>
         <p>Historically, when one wants to transact money, they have relied on intermediaries such as banks to guarantee security and trust. These intermediaries are central authorites which have complete control of one's money and verify who owns what. But what if these intermediaries are not nessecary? What if there is no reliance on a centralized single party nessecary to guarantee trust? What is the whole system was governed by economic inventives, cryptography, and computer science?    </p>
         <h5> Introducing Bitcoin</h5>
         <p> Bitcoin a digital currency which is decentralized, simply meaning there is no one person with much control.</p>
